HEADWORD: Heterogony
<hw>Het`er*og"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ offspring.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The condition of having two or more kinds of flowers, different as
to the length of their stamens and pistils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

